cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the deployment of UAVs as flying base stations for on-demand coverage in a downlink network. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper deals with the deployment of UAVs in a 3D space. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a distributed algorithm for the collaborative deployment of UAVs. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a sensing-aided crowd density estimation method. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the optimization of coverage in a wireless network.
